# Jikan Removal and Client Unification Implementation Plan

We will consolidate backend host/port resolving logic, remove duplication, and route all proxy queries through a single, unified client tier.

## Proposed Changes

### API Layer

#### [NEW] [apiClient.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/src/services/api/apiClient.ts)
- Implement unified host discovery bridging (supports `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` in production, falls back to dynamic IP address discovery on emulators/devices, or default 127.0.0.1 on fallback).
- Create a generic `executeBackendQuery` wrapper utility to fetch from this dynamically resolved endpoint.
- Parse and strip error models, preventing raw connection messages from leaking into the UI.

#### [MODIFY] [JikanAdapter.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/src/services/api/JikanAdapter.ts)
- Strip duplicate [getBackendBaseUrl](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/src/services/RecommendationService.ts#5-16) and [executeRestQuery](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/src/services/api/JikanAdapter.ts#25-40) methods.
- Import `executeBackendQuery` and `BACKEND_BASE` from `apiClient.ts`.
- Clean all direct fetch implementations.

#### [MODIFY] [RecommendationService.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/src/services/RecommendationService.ts)
- Strip duplicated URL resolution code.
- Import `BACKEND_BASE` / `executeBackendQuery` directly.

## Verification Plan

### Automated / Manual Verification
- Compile the TypeScript application.
- Launch the Expo app (`npm run start`).
- Confirm all pages (Home, Search, Details) load data correctly from the backend proxy.
